description:
2015-16 Public Charter Schools - Number of Students on Wait Lists by Campus

1.	These figures are up to date as of March 27th (Round 1 results day) and are subject to change throughout the spring.
2.	Many students are on multiple waiting lists, which can happen for two reasons. First, students are waitlisted at schools they rank above the school to which they are matched. Second, applicants are waitlisted if the applicant’s sibling is matched through the lottery. An applicant will be placed on the waitlist of any school they ranked below their match when their sibling is matched with that school. For example, if a student is matched with their 2nd choice school, the student will automatically  be placed on the waitlist of their 3rd choice school if their sibling was matched with that same (3rd choice) school. 
3.	A waitlist at a school does not indicate that there are no open seats available. Please contact schools for the most up-to-date information.
4.	In the waitlist data file, “.” indicates that no data were reported for the school; “N/A” indicates that the school doesn’t serve the grade or that the school doesn’t accept applications in the grade”; and “0” indicates that there aren’t any names on the waitlist.
title: Wait List (SY15-16) as of March 27th, 2015
